What is APR?
yes

APR stands for Annual Percentage Rate. It's a measure of the annual cost of borrowing money, expressed as a percentage rate. This includes not only the interest you pay on your loan but also any fees associated with getting that loan. APR helps consumers compare different loan offers more accurately because it provides a consistent basis for comparing costs across various lenders and types of loans. It's crucial to consider when evaluating the true cost of borrowing money over a year.
